The paper deals with a machine learning problem of reciprocal recommendation, which involves predicting a match between two users based on their preferences. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Given that the paper focuses on designing and analyzing an algorithm for efficient learning in the reciprocal recommendation task, cs.LG and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses general limitations and assumptions of the problem, which could fall under cs.SI and cs.AI. Finally, the algorithmic approach and performance evaluation could involve techniques from cs.DS.
